55 template<class Archive>
56 void Object::Data::load(Archive &ar) {
57  ar & V_NAME(ar, "meta", meta);
58  attributes.clear();
59  StdAttributeMap attrMap;
60  ar & V_NAME(ar, "attributes", attrMap);
61  for (auto &kv: attrMap) {
62  auto &a = kv.first;
63  auto &vallist = kv.second;
64  setAttributeList(a, vallist);
65  }
66 }

76 template<class Archive>
77 Object *Object::loadObject(Archive &ar) {
78 
79  Object *obj = nullptr;
80  try {
81  std::string arname;
82  ar & V_NAME(ar, "object_name", arname);
83  std::string name = ar.translateObjectName(arname);
84  int type;
85  ar & V_NAME(ar, "object_type", type);
86  Shm::the().lockObjects();
87  Object::Data *objData = nullptr;
88  if (!name.empty())
89  objData = Shm::the().getObjectDataFromName(name);
90  if (objData && objData->isComplete()) {
91  objData->ref();
92  Shm::the().unlockObjects();
93  obj = Object::create(objData);
94  if (!ar.currentObject())
95  ar.setCurrentObject(objData);
96  objData->unref();
97  assert(obj->refcount() >= 1);
98  } else {
99  if (objData) {
100  std::cerr << "Object::loadObject: have " << name << ", but incomplete, refcount=" << objData->refcount() << std::endl;
101  }
102  Shm::the().unlockObjects();
103  auto funcs = ObjectTypeRegistry::getType(type);
104  obj = funcs.createEmpty(name);
105  name = obj->getName();
106  ar.registerObjectNameTranslation(arname, name);
107  obj->loadFromArchive(ar);
108  assert(obj->refcount() >= 1);
109  }
110 #ifdef USE_BOOST_ARCHIVE
111  } catch (const boost::archive::archive_exception &ex) {
112  std::cerr << "Boost.Archive exception: " << ex.what() << std::endl;
113  if (ex.code == boost::archive::archive_exception::unsupported_version) {
114  std::cerr << "***" << std::endl;
115  std::cerr << "*** received Boost archive in unsupported format, supported is up to " << boost::archive::BOOST_ARCHIVE_VERSION() << std::endl;
116  std::cerr << "***" << std::endl;
117  }
118  return obj;
119 #endif
120  } catch (std::exception &ex) {
121  std::cerr << "exception during object loading: " << ex.what() << std::endl;
122  return obj;
123  } catch (...) {
124  throw;
125  }
126  assert(ar.currentObject() == obj->d());
127  if (obj->d()->unresolvedReferences == 0) {
128  obj->refresh();
129  obj->check();
130  if (ar.objectCompletionHandler())
131  ar.objectCompletionHandler()();
132  } else {
133  //std::cerr << "LOADED " << obj->d()->name << " (" << obj->d()->type << "): " << obj->d()->unresolvedReferences << " unresolved references" << std::endl;
134  }
135  return obj;
136 }
